  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BUILDING PAINTER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Prepare and paint walls and surfaces by scraping, filling cracks, mixing paint, and applying finishes to meet quality standards and project specifications.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare walls and surfaces by scraping, sanding, and removing old paint to ensure proper adhesion of new coatings</li><li>Fill cracks and holes with appropriate materials such as plaster to create smooth surfaces</li><li>Mix paint and other materials to achieve the correct color and texture according to project requirements</li><li>Apply paint, varnish, and other finishes using brushes, rollers, caulking guns, and other tools following instructions</li><li>Calculate painting costs and negotiate prices to support project budgeting and client agreements</li><li>Follow all health and safety precautions to maintain a safe work environment</li><li>Use manual dexterity and balance to work safely on scaffolding, ladders, and other elevated platforms</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience as a painter demonstrating ability to complete painting tasks effectively</li><li>Knowledge of painting materials, including selection, mixing, and application techniques</li><li>Understanding of commercial and/or construction painting methods</li><li>Ability to use painting tools such as brushes and caulking guns with precision</li><li>Physical ability to maintain balance and manual dexterity while working at heights</li><li>Flexibility to work after regular hours, on weekends, public holidays, and any shift (night/day) as needed</li></ul>",
